The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, May 01, 2004 				 EC scanner on PM seat
																								New Delhi, April 30: The Election Commission today ordered video recording of polling in 14 sensitive constituencies  including Lucknow, Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayees constituency  in Uttar Pradesh, reports our special correspondent. 																								The high-profile list also includes Mainpuri, Mulayam Singh Yadavs constituency, Allahabad, from where human resource development minister Murli Manohar Joshi is contesting, Sambhal, Mulayam Singhs son Akhileshs constituency, and Kanuj, where his brother Ram Gopal Yadav is in the fray.																								The other seats on the list are Baghpat, Etawah, Hathras, Firozabad, Badaun, Banda, Bulandshahr, Meerut and Sitapur.																								After the fracas over polls in Chhapra and Siwan, the commission does not want to take a risk. It has appointed two inspectors-general of police to monitor security arrangements across Uttar Pradesh on May 5 and 10. 
